'''Reinhold Geijer''' (born 1953 in [[Sundsvall]], Sweden)is CEO of Nordisk Renting<ref>[http://www.affarsvarlden.se/hem/nyheter/article247875.ece Nytt VD-jobb för Reinhold Geijer], ''[[Affärsvärlden]]'' 2001-06-13 {{sv icon}}</ref> and Head of the Nordic Region for the [[Royal Bank of Scotland]].

Geijer is a descendant of Erik Gustaf Reinhold Geijer (born 1917) and Sigrid Margareta Sophie Cavalli (born 1921). Reinhold Geijer is married to Lena Kristina Linhard and  they have two sons.

Geijer holds an MSc in Business Administration from [[Stockholm School of Economics]] and has worked in the banking sector at [[Föreningssparbanken]], where he was [[CEO]]. He has also studied the [[Harvard Business School]]’s Executive Program. Geijer was Chairman of BU Europe Transition Group for separating [[ABN AMRO]] into the Consortium Banks: [[Royal Bank of Scotland]], [[Fortis (finance)|Fortis]] and [[Banco Santander|Santander]].

